msgid ""
"\\subsection*{Turn Order}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/round_structure.tex:91
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"After the start of the Round, players take Turns in a clockwise order as described in the next section.\n"
"After all players have played their Turn, move the Black Cube on the Round Tracker one space forward and perform the start of Round again.\n"
"Keep playing new Rounds until any of the Scenario's ending conditions have been met.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/round_structure.tex:96
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid ""
#| "\\note{6}{\n"
#| "  In the Alliance game, teams take turns alternately.\n"
#| "  At the start of your team's first turn of the Round, choose who goes first and last in that Round.\n"
#| "}\n"
#| "\n"
msgid ""
"\\note{6}{\n"
"  In the \\textbf{Alliance game}, teams take turns alternately.\n"
"  At the start of your team's first turn of the Round, choose who goes first and last in that Round.\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"\\note{6}{\n"
"  En juego de Alianza, los equipos toman turnos alternados.\n"
"  Al inicio del primer turno de tu equipo en la Ronda, elije quién jugará primero en esa Ronda.\n"
"}\n"
"\n"

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/round_structure.tex:98
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\subsection*{Example Round}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"\\vspace*{-2em}\n"
"\\subsection*{Example Round}\n"
"\n"

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/round_structure.tex:103
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\textit{Alice is playing as the Tower Faction against Bob playing as the Dungeon Faction.\n"
"Alice is the starting player.\n"
"They are about to start the \\nth{5} Round.\n"
"}\\par\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/round_structure.tex:107
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\textit{Before anything else, both players flip their Build, Population, and Spell Book Tokens back to their active side.\n"
"All Movement Tokens are flipped back to their active, green~\\svg[12]{movement_token_green} sides.\n"
"Both players also regain the use of their Expert Effects \\svg{expert}.}\\par\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/round_structure.tex:110
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\textit{Round 5 is an odd-numbered Round, and not the first, so it is a \\textbf{Resource Round}.\n"
"Both players collect income from their Buildings, Mines, and Settlements.}\\par\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/round_structure.tex:117
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\textit{Since both Alice and Bob have City Halls built, they resolve their ``At the beginning of each Resource Round'' effects.\n"
"The \\wikilink{/towns/tower/\\#fully-built}{Tower City Hall} allows Alice to either gain 4~\\svg{gold} or draw a card from her Deck.\n"
"She chooses the latter.\n"
"The \\wikilink{/towns/dungeon/\\#fully-built}{Dungeon City Hall} gives Bob the option to gain extra 5~\\svg{gold} or 1~\\svg{valuables}.\n"
"Bob chooses the former.\n"
"}\\par\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/round_structure.tex:122
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\begin{expansion}{fortress}\n"
"\\textit{Since this is a Resource Round, an Event card should now be drawn from the Event Deck.\n"
"  The drawing responsibility rotates clockwise after each Event: Alice, as the starting player, drew the first Event back in Round 3.}\\par\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/round_structure.tex:126
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\end{expansion}\n"
"\\begin{expansion}{fortress}\n"
"\\textit{It is therefore Bob's turn to draw. He takes the top card from the Event Deck, reads it aloud, and places it face-up so both players can see: it is \\textbf{Artifact Merchant} (see the Event card on the previous page).}\\par\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/round_structure.tex:138
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\vspace*{0.5em}\n"
"\\textit{Bob draws 5 cards from the top of the Artifact Deck, revealing them to both players.\n"
"Among them there is a Major Artifact -- the \\wikilink{artifacts/head_of_legion}{Head of Legion.}\n"
"Bob goes first, as the player who drew the Event.\n"
"  He immediately purchases the Head of Legion, pays 5~\\svg{gold} (putting the gold from the City Hall to good use) and adds it to his Deck.\n"
"He passes the remaining cards to Alice.\n"
"Alice had also wanted the Head of Legion, but it is already gone.\n"
"She is not interested in the remaining cards, therefore she passes.\n"
"Since the cards have now returned to the player who drew them, the Event ends.\n"
"The remaining Artifacts are shuffled back into the Artifact Deck.}\\par\n"
"\\end{expansion}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/round_structure.tex:143
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\vspace*{0.5em}\n"
"\\textit{Round 5 also has a timed Event marked on the Round Tracker: Scenario specifies that all Heroes gain +1~\\svg{movement} this Round.\n"
"Bob controls only his Main Hero, so only one extra MP is added, increasing their \\svg{movement} from 3 to 4.\n"
"Because Alice controls both a Main Hero and a Secondary Hero, \\textbf{both} of them benefit -- their movement goes to 4 and 3, respectively.}\\par\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/round_structure.tex:145
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\textit{As a starting player, Alice now starts her Turn.}\\par\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

